I"i<p>Global macro is generated by the following code:</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>cap global dir = "C:\Users\liang\Desktop\111523-V2\aer_replication"
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Local macros only exist either in the current session, or in the current do file (if the do file is run once).</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">macro list</code> will list all the current macros.</p>

<p>To substitute the macro contents of a global macro name, the macro name is typed (punctuated)
with a dollar sign ($) in front.</p>
